lore.First_Edict_Of_The_Uplic_Sovereign.title = First Edict of the Uplic Sovereign
lore.First_Edict_Of_The_Uplic_Sovereign.author = Principality Severus, Scribe of the Heavens
lore.First_Edict_Of_The_Uplic_Sovereign.page0.text = Unto that which lay entombed in the abyss. All loyal to the sacrosanct covenant of the heavens heed this call; The denizens of Nytha pledge their fealty to the Mother of the Depths. Sanctification of these despoiled grounds must commence, rend these heretics; split flesh from bone, body from soul. Such is the Uplic Sovereign's edict, and unto all ye faithful shall it be fulfilled.

lore.Cry_Of_The_Heavens.title = Cry of the Heavens
lore.Cry_Of_The_Heavens.author = Commander Vauch
lore.Cry_Of_The_Heavens.page0.text = Oh look upon these wretches! They pray to their archdevil still yet! That wench of blood and bone, defiler of life and death! It is by the Uplic Sovereign's DEMAND that we split their skulls in two! Faithful, hear me now! We shall end the Nythan scum, and sanctify the Abyss which they call home! GRANT THEM NO REFUGE, NO RESPITE! THIS IS OUR COMMAND, AND WE SHALL FULFILL IT! FOR THE SOVEREIGN!

lore.Oh_Forgotten_Nytha.title = Oh, Forgotten Nytha
lore.Oh_Forgotten_Nytha.author = Arastetes
lore.Oh_Forgotten_Nytha.page0.text = Oh, Forgotten Nytha.\nOh, Sovereign of the Depths.\nWhere now rest the Bythe?\nOnce upon the Welig steppes.\nFor heavens cast cloying gaze,\nunto Nytha's splendor.\nThose divine sought to raze,\nthat yet still tender.

lore.Lament_Of_The_Disillusioned.title = Lament of the DisillusionedS
lore.Lament_Of_The_Disillusioned.author = Desmonda Bythe
lore.Lament_Of_The_Disillusioned.page0.text = Curse the Sovereign upon their alabaster throne. Curse the angels in their marble halls. Damn the heavens gilded in quartz. Spurn the god which reign from ivory spire. Light so righteous, yet not did they care. Saught to oust our Queen for naught but their pride. She who made us in our craddle, hated by all for origins abyssal. The angels claim us, yet it was the demons who brought life; demons that nurtured us.

lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.title = Testament of the Matriarch
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.author = Elder Lich Vy'Lax Bythe
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page0.text = Let it be known, through all of Nytha, that the Matriarch still breathes. The heavens try yet in vain to snap the horns of the Sovereign of the Depths, and shall continue to do so. In the face of this inquisition, the Matriarch shall bring them what they sow. All of Nytha know this, the Last Candle...
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page1.text = ...can be found within the depths of the last stronghold. Through there we shall find refuge, and all of Nytha shall yet be saved. So do not yet find despair, the angels can not take from us what they can not lay their cloying gaze upon. Further into the depths must we descend, but the Abyss...
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page2.text = ...can not hide us from the eyes of the divine for eternity. Thus it has fallen upon the Great Lord Vernaken to gaurd the tomb till Nytha is but from a time immemorial to the heavens. Their sacrifice shall be what keeps our safety assured, and along with them, the Nythan Fifth Regiment shall remain...
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page3.text = ...to assist the Lord. Pay respects now for them while they still walk amongst us, for this shall be the last you will see of them. They will guard us till the flesh sloughs from their bones, and even then their bodies will not still. Such is the dedication of the Nythan people, though we may yet lose the Wileg...
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page4.text = ...steppes, our lives have yet to end. For was it not she who granted us the knowledge of life and death? Was it not in her name that we learned the art of necromancy? Nay, we Nythans are not so weak willed that we shall let the Holy Tyrants conquer us so, we shall fight till our last, so that Nythans may once...
lore.Testament_Of_The_Matriarch.page5.text = ...more know peace, even if the cost is our own lives, we shall pay it, and we shall pay it in full. Let the angels know the will of the Nythans! The heavens shall have no power of the Bythe! For the Matriarch still breathes, and the Uplic Sovereign has not the power to change that as long as we draw breath!

lore.Sacred_Rights.title = Sacred Rights
lore.Sacred_Rights.author = Principality Severus, Scribe of the Heavens
lore.Sacred_Rights.page0.text = Oh now see, those yet still breathing, cast thy gaze towards the heavens. Children of the sacrosanct covenant, let air yet pure expunge thy lungs of sin's miasma. Let not the festering pestulance find root in the heart that is thine. Such vile, putrid things are an offront to the Sovereign, and thy untainted soul. Bring thy self back to center, and once more cast eyes upon all which is empyrean in form.
